## ğŸ³ **ARCHITETTURA DOCKER COMPOSE - ISOLAMENTO COMPLETO**

```yaml
version: '3.8'
services:
  # Database - SOLO INTERNO
  postgres:
    image: postgres:15
    # NESSUNA PORTA ESPOSTA ESTERNAMENTE
    expose: ["5432"]  # Solo visibile nel network interno
    environment:
      POSTGRES_DB: springmon_auth
      POSTGRES_USER: springmon
      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: password
    volumes:
      - postgres_data:/var/lib/postgresql/data
      - ./database/init.sql:/docker-entrypoint-initdb.d/init.sql
    networks:
      - springmon-internal

  # Redis - SOLO INTERNO
  redis:
    image: redis:7-alpine
    # NESSUNA PORTA ESPOSTA ESTERNAMENTE
    expose: ["6379"]  # Solo visibile nel network interno
    networks:
      - springmon-internal

  # Auth Service - SOLO INTERNO
  auth-service:
    build: ./auth-service
    # NESSUNA PORTA ESPOSTA ESTERNAMENTE
    expose: ["8081"]  # Solo visibile nel network interno
    depends_on: [postgres, redis]
    environment:
      DB_HOST: postgres
      DB_PORT: 5432
      REDIS_HOST: redis
    networks:
      - springmon-internal

  # Gateway Service - UNICO ACCESSO ESTERNO
  gateway-service:
    build: ./gateway-service
    ports: ["8080:8080"]  # UNICA PORTA ESPOSTA
    depends_on: [auth-service]
    environment:
      AUTH_SERVICE_URL: http://auth-service:8081
      REDIS_HOST: redis
    networks:
      - springmon-internal

networks:
  springmon-internal:
    driver: bridge
    internal: false  # Permette accesso esterno solo al gateway

volumes:
  postgres_data:
```

### **ğŸ” FLUSSO DI SICUREZZA**
```
ğŸŒ CLIENT â†’ ğŸšª GATEWAY (8080) â†’ ğŸ” AUTH-SERVICE â†’ ğŸ—„ï¸ POSTGRES
                    â†“
              ğŸ”’ JWT TOKEN VALIDATION
                    â†“
              ğŸ“¦ BUSINESS SERVICES (futuri)
```

